comments.text:
This is one of those scenes where, you, after years upon years of 
movie-viewing experience where you've seen jaw dropping special effects, 
thrilling plotlines, and heard invigorating scores... you cannot deny how 
bloody effective this scene is to making you laugh.
I haven't seen this film in little over a decade and I'm laughing so hard 
that my back is aching, I'm out of breath, and I'm in tears.

You may hate toilet humor but it tickles that really REALLY primitive part 
of your mind which for some damn reason loves fart sounds and cliche 
dysfunctional families.﻿
